1
00:00:28,822 --> 00:00:29,982
What is the status?

2
00:00:30,224 --> 00:00:31,792
The area has been expanding at
a constant rate

3
00:00:31,792 --> 00:00:32,952
since we first started monitoring it.

4
00:00:33,594 --> 00:00:35,994
The Stealth Force is already
on its way to investigate.

5
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:38,397
They should be entering
the area shortly.

6
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,622
I've just established contact.

7
00:00:41,201 --> 00:00:43,604
They'll be passing by the Dangai
Precipice World in ten seconds.

8
00:00:43,604 --> 00:00:45,504
They're about to enter
the dimensional area.

9
00:00:46,673 --> 00:00:47,867
Opening communication lines.

10
00:00:51,378 --> 00:00:53,573
Hey! What...?! The exit!

11
00:00:55,749 --> 00:00:56,875
We have an emergency!

12
00:00:57,451 --> 00:00:59,476
We've failed to infiltrate the area!

13
00:00:59,786 --> 00:01:02,122
Requesting immediate back up!
I repeat!

14
00:01:02,122 --> 00:01:03,350
We have an emergency!

15
00:01:03,390 --> 00:01:05,259
- The infiltration has failed!
- Research Technology Commcenter here.

16
00:01:05,259 --> 00:01:06,660
We copy your back up request.

17
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:07,820
This is Research
Technology Commcenter...

18
00:01:07,861 --> 00:01:09,590
Requesting emergency opening
of Senkaimon.

19
00:01:09,963 --> 00:01:12,733
Members of the Stealth Force
have failed to infiltrate the area!

20
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:15,031
- Notify Central 46 immediately!
- They have been left behind...

21
00:01:15,068 --> 00:01:16,194
- Move!
- In the Dangai Precipice World.

22
00:01:16,270 --> 00:01:18,363
We'll be swallowed up by
the Restrictive Current!

23
00:01:18,472 --> 00:01:19,907
Hey! Can you hear me?

24
00:01:19,907 --> 00:01:23,240
Why can't you infiltrate the area?
Tell us!

25
00:02:27,908 --> 00:02:29,398
- Get ready!
- Right!

26
00:02:32,412 --> 00:02:33,310
Hey!

27
00:02:49,296 --> 00:02:50,194
You're not getting away!

28
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,331
Not so easy!

29
00:03:41,815 --> 00:03:42,577
Ichigo!

30
00:03:46,186 --> 00:03:49,280
It seems that Hollow
was after this child.

31
00:03:55,328 --> 00:03:58,422
It's all right. He only looks scary.

32
00:03:58,532 --> 00:03:59,556
Shut up!

33
00:04:01,902 --> 00:04:03,130
All right then, let's go.

34
00:04:03,937 --> 00:04:05,238
Don't worry.

35
00:04:05,238 --> 00:04:08,139
Soul Society is not a scary place.

36
00:04:09,042 --> 00:04:10,634
It's where all the souls
come from.

37
00:04:12,679 --> 00:04:13,441
But...

38
00:04:14,648 --> 00:04:16,616
If you stay here...

39
00:04:16,616 --> 00:04:19,084
another monster like that
will come after you.

40
00:05:10,403 --> 00:05:11,563
Is it over already?

41
00:05:11,705 --> 00:05:12,535
Yes.

42
00:05:13,073 --> 00:05:13,971
Thanks.

43
00:05:16,276 --> 00:05:17,265
Ichigo!

44
00:05:17,344 --> 00:05:18,311
Huh?

45
00:05:19,112 --> 00:05:21,273
Don't use your Combat Pass
so freely.

46
00:05:21,581 --> 00:05:23,105
Huh? Why?

47
00:05:24,818 --> 00:05:26,115
Oww!

48
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,744
What's the big idea?!

49
00:05:32,225 --> 00:05:34,022
You have him.

50
00:05:34,494 --> 00:05:37,364
You keep leaving your body
here and there,

51
00:05:37,364 --> 00:05:39,924
and thanks to that, I'm the one who has
to deal with the messy aftermath.

52
00:05:40,066 --> 00:05:41,033
Why's that?

53
00:05:41,101 --> 00:05:42,329
For example...

54
00:05:42,636 --> 00:05:44,399
A passerby approaches.

55
00:05:44,538 --> 00:05:49,566
"Excuse me, is something wrong?
Oh no, this man isn't breathing!"

56
00:05:49,976 --> 00:05:53,935
"Ambulance. No, if he's dead,
I must get a hearse!"

57
00:05:54,614 --> 00:05:55,672
Get the idea?

58
00:05:55,782 --> 00:05:57,909
Like they'd call a hearse!

59
00:05:58,151 --> 00:05:59,286
That's not the point!

60
00:05:59,286 --> 00:06:02,983
In any case, it's a big hassle
if there's a commotion.

61
00:06:03,056 --> 00:06:03,818
Huh?

62
00:06:04,558 --> 00:06:06,753
Hurry! He's in cardiac arrest!

63
00:06:08,228 --> 00:06:09,320
Too late...

64
00:06:09,496 --> 00:06:11,225
M My body!

65
00:06:12,832 --> 00:06:14,356
Oh, look!

66
00:06:14,434 --> 00:06:16,402
What's going on?!

67
00:06:16,503 --> 00:06:17,765
He's alive!

68
00:06:18,004 --> 00:06:18,732
You...!

69
00:06:18,872 --> 00:06:20,396
Uh, hi.

70
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:21,672
Are you all right?

71
00:06:23,610 --> 00:06:25,100
You still need to lie down!

72
00:06:25,212 --> 00:06:26,440
I'm telling you, I'm fine!

73
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,912
- Hey, hold him down! He's delirious!
- Stop it!

74
00:06:28,949 --> 00:06:29,938
Really...

75
00:06:39,626 --> 00:06:41,184
Man, that was bad.

76
00:06:41,294 --> 00:06:42,921
That's my line!

77
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:45,532
You're lucky I had
my Memory Replacement

78
00:06:45,532 --> 00:06:47,193
to switch everyone's memory.

79
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:47,990
Kon!

80
00:06:48,235 --> 00:06:49,463
Yes, yes!

81
00:06:50,003 --> 00:06:50,628
Hey...

82
00:06:51,371 --> 00:06:52,072
What's with you?!

83
00:06:52,072 --> 00:06:54,836
- Why, Sis?!
- There's no point unless you hold him!

84
00:06:55,308 --> 00:06:56,710
- No, no way!
- Why do I wanna...!

85
00:06:56,710 --> 00:06:58,302
Sis, I absolutely...!

86
00:06:59,079 --> 00:06:59,909
Shut up!

87
00:07:01,881 --> 00:07:02,540
What?

88
00:07:02,649 --> 00:07:05,051
- S Stop! I'll get dirty!
- Shut up!

89
00:07:05,051 --> 00:07:06,814
There's dog poop over there!

90
00:07:06,853 --> 00:07:07,945
Hope it sticks to you!

91
00:07:08,088 --> 00:07:09,953
What's the meaning of this?

92
00:07:10,457 --> 00:07:12,322
What? Another Hollow?

93
00:07:12,826 --> 00:07:13,520
Take this!

94
00:07:14,694 --> 00:07:16,286
It got in my mouth!

95
00:07:16,563 --> 00:07:17,393
Ichigo...

96
00:07:18,198 --> 00:07:19,859
Serves you right!

97
00:07:19,966 --> 00:07:22,196
Why you!
You've done it this time!

98
00:07:22,302 --> 00:07:24,293
- S Stop! My stuffing's gonna fall out!
- Hey!

99
00:07:24,337 --> 00:07:25,964
Wait! I'm dealing with him...

100
00:07:26,206 --> 00:07:27,104
Huh?

101
00:07:28,642 --> 00:07:29,574
The train station!

102
00:07:29,876 --> 00:07:30,638
Hey!

103
00:07:33,647 --> 00:07:35,012
What's with this Spiritual Pressure?

104
00:07:35,348 --> 00:07:36,246
I don't know.

105
00:07:36,683 --> 00:07:38,844
I've never experienced this kind
of Spiritual Pressure before.

106
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,289
What the hell are they?

107
00:08:22,595 --> 00:08:24,495
White ghosts?!

108
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,724
No one else can see them.

109
00:08:29,869 --> 00:08:31,063
They must be spirit beings.

110
00:08:31,604 --> 00:08:34,198
But they don't have chains
on their chests.

111
00:08:34,874 --> 00:08:35,772
What's...

112
00:08:36,042 --> 00:08:37,134
We have no choice.

113
00:08:37,844 --> 00:08:39,539
What? Again?

114
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:42,140
Use him!

115
00:08:44,451 --> 00:08:46,419
Huh?! Hey, what...?!

116
00:08:48,355 --> 00:08:49,447
Disgusting...

117
00:08:54,094 --> 00:08:55,959
Kon! Go hide somewhere!

118
00:08:56,896 --> 00:08:57,920
Hey!

119
00:08:58,031 --> 00:08:59,658
Hey, don't leave me!

120
00:09:01,134 --> 00:09:03,364
Hey, what are you doing?!

121
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:06,172
This is Rukia Kuchiki of Squad 13,

122
00:09:06,172 --> 00:09:08,504
in World of the Living area 3888!

123
00:09:08,575 --> 00:09:09,405
Rukia!

124
00:09:09,442 --> 00:09:11,569
Ichigo, try performing a Konso!

125
00:09:11,678 --> 00:09:13,043
What?! A Konso?!

126
00:09:13,113 --> 00:09:14,239
Reporting on the situation!

127
00:09:14,781 --> 00:09:17,250
- Unidentified spirit beings...
- What the hell... It's worth a try.

128
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:18,911
Possessing spiritual power
have appeared in large numbers.

129
00:09:24,124 --> 00:09:25,682
No good Rukia!
It's not working on these guys...

130
00:09:25,925 --> 00:09:29,452
Wait! My connection with Soul Society...

131
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:39,431
What's going on?! Huh?

132
00:09:41,141 --> 00:09:42,574
Huh?! Stop!

133
00:09:42,642 --> 00:09:43,540
Rukia!

134
00:09:45,011 --> 00:09:48,640
What's this all of a sudden?!
Stop! Stop!

135
00:09:48,848 --> 00:09:50,873
What's the deal with you guys?!
Move it!

136
00:09:54,387 --> 00:09:55,376
What'll we do?

137
00:09:55,855 --> 00:09:56,787
Well...

138
00:10:04,364 --> 00:10:05,194
What the?!

139
00:10:15,608 --> 00:10:16,597
A Soul Reaper?!

140
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:18,668
What are you doing?!

141
00:10:19,412 --> 00:10:20,344
Hey!

142
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,951
Oww! Oww!
Hey, don't step on me!

143
00:10:34,327 --> 00:10:35,259
Huh?!

144
00:10:36,896 --> 00:10:38,295
What's that?

145
00:10:48,274 --> 00:10:50,265
She's going to release her zanpaku to!

146
00:10:50,376 --> 00:10:51,274
What?!

147
00:10:51,878 --> 00:10:53,436
Bring them to the twilight...

148
00:10:57,183 --> 00:10:58,013
Ichigo!

149
00:10:58,651 --> 00:11:01,313
Stop! What the hell are you doing?!

150
00:11:01,654 --> 00:11:03,622
Those things aren't Hollows!

151
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:05,623
Shut your mouth, stupid!

152
00:11:05,658 --> 00:11:06,454
Stu...?!

153
00:11:11,297 --> 00:11:13,663
Hey! You stepped on my face...

154
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,494
Bring them to the twilight!

155
00:11:16,803 --> 00:11:17,929
Mirokumaru!

156
00:11:24,944 --> 00:11:25,876
What?!

157
00:11:26,312 --> 00:11:28,576
Now what?

158
00:11:30,016 --> 00:11:32,280
Huh? What happened to
that other guy?

159
00:11:53,907 --> 00:11:57,365
Sorry to keep you waiting!
Wasn't that wind so strong?

160
00:12:04,717 --> 00:12:06,184
What's going on?

161
00:12:06,286 --> 00:12:07,020
They vanished.

162
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:08,749
Yes! That was awesome!

163
00:12:09,522 --> 00:12:13,288
Yes, yes, yes! That felt so good!

164
00:12:14,861 --> 00:12:16,726
Oh, it's you.

165
00:12:18,598 --> 00:12:19,565
YOU!

166
00:12:19,832 --> 00:12:22,562
H How'd you change into
your gigai so quickly?

167
00:12:22,869 --> 00:12:23,836
I dunno.

168
00:12:23,836 --> 00:12:25,428
Just who are you?

169
00:12:25,838 --> 00:12:26,896
I'm a Soul Reaper.

170
00:12:27,340 --> 00:12:29,001
I know that!

171
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:32,572
If you want to know someone's name,
shouldn't you introduce yourself first?

172
00:12:34,547 --> 00:12:35,912
I'm Ichigo Kurosaki.

173
00:12:36,683 --> 00:12:38,275
Oh, you're pretty obedient.

174
00:12:38,651 --> 00:12:40,920
My name is Senna. Later!

175
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,182
Don't "Later" me!

176
00:12:42,589 --> 00:12:44,056
Why'd you do such a thing?

177
00:12:44,457 --> 00:12:45,981
Why not?

178
00:12:46,492 --> 00:12:49,154
Do you know something
about those things?

179
00:12:50,997 --> 00:12:52,198
Hey! What's the matter?

180
00:12:52,198 --> 00:12:53,995
This is bad! I knew it!

181
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,164
What is it?!

182
00:12:56,169 --> 00:12:59,969
Hmm... Yellow just isn't my color.

183
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:02,940
Never mind that. Come!

184
00:13:03,977 --> 00:13:05,137
Ichigo, right?

185
00:13:05,311 --> 00:13:06,073
Yeah.

186
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:08,442
- Over there!
- Huh?

187
00:13:08,881 --> 00:13:10,283
There's an unconscious man...

188
00:13:10,283 --> 00:13:12,485
in front of the train station.
Requesting an ambulance immediately!

189
00:13:12,485 --> 00:13:14,476
Kon! Not again!

190
00:13:14,687 --> 00:13:16,552
See, you better hurry!

191
00:13:16,956 --> 00:13:19,254
Not so fast! Come with me!

192
00:13:19,692 --> 00:13:20,716
Hey!

193
00:13:20,927 --> 00:13:22,360
I just want to ask you some questions!

194
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:24,990
The fool...

195
00:13:47,086 --> 00:13:48,451
Give up already?

196
00:13:49,589 --> 00:13:50,920
You gotta be kidding!

197
00:13:52,325 --> 00:13:54,193
I don't know...

198
00:13:54,193 --> 00:13:55,895
You really think it's okay
for a lieutenant

199
00:13:55,895 --> 00:13:57,123
to be drinking in
the middle of the day?

200
00:13:57,930 --> 00:14:01,422
What're you saying?
This is like drinking water.

201
00:14:01,868 --> 00:14:03,836
Hey! It's emptied out already.

202
00:14:03,836 --> 00:14:05,804
What?! Not again!

203
00:14:06,005 --> 00:14:08,599
You drink too much,
you shaded geezer!

204
00:14:09,142 --> 00:14:10,769
Shut up, baldie!

205
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,400
What?!

206
00:14:12,679 --> 00:14:13,846
Wanna go another round?!

207
00:14:13,846 --> 00:14:17,714
Fine! Whoever loses gets the sake.
Got it?!

208
00:14:20,119 --> 00:14:21,643
Taking the high ground again?

209
00:14:22,922 --> 00:14:24,389
The quicker one gets it!

210
00:14:25,558 --> 00:14:27,890
Whatever. Here I...

211
00:14:28,294 --> 00:14:29,022
Huh?

212
00:14:31,764 --> 00:14:32,924
What's the matter?!

213
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:35,230
What is that thing?

214
00:14:50,283 --> 00:14:52,376
A Ferris wheel! Look!

215
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,385
I didn't know they had
one of these here.

216
00:14:59,058 --> 00:15:00,286
Wow...

217
00:15:02,428 --> 00:15:04,396
Anyway, what were you saying?

218
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:05,863
What squad do you belong to?!

219
00:15:06,065 --> 00:15:08,533
I don't remember such things.

220
00:15:09,235 --> 00:15:11,669
Hmm... What squad did I belong to?

221
00:15:12,171 --> 00:15:13,306
Listen here.

222
00:15:13,306 --> 00:15:16,409
You wield a zanpaku to
and know how to release it.

223
00:15:16,409 --> 00:15:18,809
There is no question that
you are a Soul Reaper.

224
00:15:19,245 --> 00:15:22,442
And if you are a Soul Reaper,
you must belong to a squad!

225
00:15:22,815 --> 00:15:24,442
How can you not remember that?

226
00:15:24,684 --> 00:15:26,049
Question, please!

227
00:15:26,486 --> 00:15:28,681
Why are you here?

228
00:15:29,689 --> 00:15:30,587
Well, that's...

229
00:15:31,991 --> 00:15:32,980
Hey!

230
00:15:33,126 --> 00:15:35,117
I said I forgot!

231
00:15:36,696 --> 00:15:37,993
What does it matter, anyway?

232
00:15:38,598 --> 00:15:41,066
Then do you know what
those guys were back there?

233
00:15:41,534 --> 00:15:42,967
Don't know that either.

234
00:15:43,703 --> 00:15:45,838
Oh, he's so cute! Can I pet him?

235
00:15:45,838 --> 00:15:46,600
Sure.

236
00:15:48,007 --> 00:15:50,669
But I thought I should
take care of them that way.

237
00:15:52,011 --> 00:15:53,069
Instinct.

238
00:15:54,447 --> 00:15:56,005
You know what I mean?

239
00:15:57,784 --> 00:15:59,149
What's with her?!

240
00:15:59,385 --> 00:16:02,479
Ichigo, I'm going to Soul Society.

241
00:16:02,688 --> 00:16:03,518
Huh?

242
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:05,348
I'm having trouble contacting them.

243
00:16:06,726 --> 00:16:09,160
And I'm concerned about
the phenomenon earlier, too.

244
00:16:09,695 --> 00:16:12,357
Do not let that girl out of your sight!

245
00:16:12,999 --> 00:16:15,601
Hey you! Trying to dump it on me!

246
00:16:15,601 --> 00:16:16,829
Sis... Not again...

247
00:16:18,171 --> 00:16:19,272
I'm counting on you.

248
00:16:19,272 --> 00:16:21,934
Boy, what's she so uptight about?

249
00:16:23,209 --> 00:16:24,676
Hey Ichigo!

250
00:16:24,811 --> 00:16:26,836
Stupid, don't shout like that here!

251
00:16:26,879 --> 00:16:27,811
She's gone!

252
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,777
What?! Dammit!

253
00:16:32,518 --> 00:16:33,416
Hey!

254
00:16:33,753 --> 00:16:35,243
Jeez, you're so persistent!

255
00:16:37,857 --> 00:16:39,518
Hey, wait!

256
00:16:46,799 --> 00:16:47,823
Hey!

257
00:16:52,605 --> 00:16:53,572
Oh?

258
00:16:56,175 --> 00:16:58,744
Remember when you told me
that if I answered your questions,

259
00:16:58,744 --> 00:17:00,234
you'd do anything I asked you to?

260
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,342
I never said anything like that!

261
00:17:03,749 --> 00:17:05,148
Let's play tag!

262
00:17:06,752 --> 00:17:08,242
Hey! I told you! I never said such thing.

263
00:17:10,189 --> 00:17:11,417
Wait!

264
00:17:16,629 --> 00:17:18,187
Jeez!

265
00:17:19,765 --> 00:17:21,255
Hey, come on out!

266
00:17:21,901 --> 00:17:22,890
Where'd you go?

267
00:17:22,969 --> 00:17:24,903
Hey, what's with all
the fun and games?

268
00:17:24,971 --> 00:17:25,494
Huh?

269
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,835
Rangiku! Toshiro!

270
00:17:30,276 --> 00:17:31,300
It's been a while...

271
00:17:31,444 --> 00:17:34,436
It's not Toshiro.
Address me as Captain Hitsugaya!

272
00:17:35,815 --> 00:17:37,749
What're you two doing here anyway?

273
00:17:38,284 --> 00:17:39,478
Wait up!

274
00:17:39,552 --> 00:17:40,644
We need to talk.

275
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:43,281
Err, well, now's not...

276
00:17:43,389 --> 00:17:44,651
Just come!

277
00:17:44,991 --> 00:17:46,117
H Hey!

278
00:17:46,759 --> 00:17:48,750
Hey! Dammit!

279
00:17:49,295 --> 00:17:52,093
I'll come back. You wait!

280
00:17:53,966 --> 00:17:56,628
That man is talking to himself.

281
00:18:02,775 --> 00:18:03,976
I see...

282
00:18:03,976 --> 00:18:06,308
Rukia went to Soul Society?

283
00:18:07,146 --> 00:18:08,579
You just missed her then.

284
00:18:09,749 --> 00:18:12,377
Well, where shall we start?

285
00:18:12,685 --> 00:18:14,487
At 12:50 a.m. Today,

286
00:18:14,487 --> 00:18:18,150
a town from the World of the Living
suddenly appeared above the Seireitei.

287
00:18:18,291 --> 00:18:20,693
At the same time, the Research
Technology Commcenter detected

288
00:18:20,693 --> 00:18:22,862
a trail of spiritual waves flowing
into the World of the Living,

289
00:18:22,862 --> 00:18:24,163
and one minute later,

290
00:18:24,163 --> 00:18:26,358
we lost all communication
between the two worlds.

291
00:18:27,934 --> 00:18:29,162
What're you talking about?

292
00:18:29,602 --> 00:18:30,660
Don't you even understand this much?

293
00:18:30,703 --> 00:18:31,965
Now now...

294
00:18:32,204 --> 00:18:34,764
I'll explain it to you in a simple manner.

295
00:18:35,241 --> 00:18:37,043
First off, our universe has two worlds,

296
00:18:37,043 --> 00:18:40,706
which are the World of the Living,
where we are, and the Soul Society.

297
00:18:40,947 --> 00:18:43,549
Between them is
the Dangai Precipice World,

298
00:18:43,549 --> 00:18:47,645
to keep the two worlds from colliding.

299
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:50,452
You ran through it once.
Remember?

300
00:18:51,023 --> 00:18:54,393
However, about three days ago,
a new dimension appeared

301
00:18:54,393 --> 00:18:57,964
between the Dangai Precipice World
and the World of the Living.

302
00:18:57,964 --> 00:18:59,165
It began to expand rapidly,

303
00:18:59,165 --> 00:19:01,793
bridging the gap and adhering
to both worlds.

304
00:19:02,335 --> 00:19:06,372
At this point, it appears the area
that attached itself is acting like a lens

305
00:19:06,372 --> 00:19:09,275
and the World of the Living is
being visible from the Soul Society,

306
00:19:09,275 --> 00:19:12,301
which is in a different dimension.

307
00:19:13,012 --> 00:19:15,606
I guess you can say it's like a mirage.

308
00:19:15,848 --> 00:19:19,418
The Stealth Force was sent out to
investigate this newly created dimension,

309
00:19:19,418 --> 00:19:20,885
but they failed.

310
00:19:21,287 --> 00:19:22,555
Our only choice now is...

311
00:19:22,555 --> 00:19:25,820
to check out the influx of spiritual waves
into the World of the Living.

312
00:19:26,292 --> 00:19:28,954
It was decided that
I would head up the operation.

313
00:19:29,295 --> 00:19:31,160
Why you?

314
00:19:32,198 --> 00:19:34,223
The other captains backed out.

315
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,864
Never mind that!

316
00:19:38,337 --> 00:19:40,271
Then it was probably those guys.

317
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:41,968
You saw something?

318
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:46,907
Yeah... hoards of 'em,
all white wearing pointy red hats.

319
00:19:47,913 --> 00:19:49,380
Blanks...

320
00:19:49,782 --> 00:19:51,477
As suspected,
the Valley of Screams.

321
00:19:51,851 --> 00:19:52,749
Huh?

322
00:19:53,719 --> 00:19:56,517
All right then.
Explanation Number Two. Ready?

323
00:19:57,923 --> 00:19:59,658
As you already know,
souls migrate between

324
00:19:59,658 --> 00:20:02,559
the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

325
00:20:02,995 --> 00:20:04,930
From time to time however,
some may, for example,

326
00:20:04,930 --> 00:20:06,732
encounter accidents
in the Dangai Precipice World

327
00:20:06,732 --> 00:20:09,633
and become detached
from this Cycle of Transmigration.

328
00:20:10,536 --> 00:20:13,406
These souls wander aimlessly
through the Dangai Precipice World

329
00:20:13,406 --> 00:20:15,931
and are slowly drawn together
over a period of time.

330
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:19,173
As the souls come together,
it causes a new dimension.

331
00:20:19,712 --> 00:20:21,407
It is known as the Valley of Screams.

332
00:20:22,348 --> 00:20:23,682
In the Valley of Screams,

333
00:20:23,682 --> 00:20:26,152
the souls separate into
memory and energy

334
00:20:26,152 --> 00:20:28,848
in preparation to return to
the Cycle of Transmigration.

335
00:20:29,955 --> 00:20:31,422
Are you following me?

336
00:20:31,524 --> 00:20:32,582
I'm following!

337
00:20:33,592 --> 00:20:39,861
Kurosaki, the ones you saw were
the souls with no memory, Blanks.

338
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:42,965
What happens to the memories?

339
00:20:43,102 --> 00:20:45,237
It's said that the memories
merge together into one entity

340
00:20:45,237 --> 00:20:48,070
and returns to the World of the Living.

341
00:20:48,207 --> 00:20:50,042
Hence, it is called a Shinenju.

342
00:20:50,042 --> 00:20:52,977
That is the name for
the collective of memories.

343
00:20:53,279 --> 00:20:54,346
In any case,

344
00:20:54,346 --> 00:20:56,649
the appearance of the Valley of Screams
is a natural phenomenon,

345
00:20:56,649 --> 00:20:59,618
and it's existence has been
verified a number of times...

346
00:21:00,052 --> 00:21:01,849
But the problem is...

347
00:21:02,288 --> 00:21:04,290
This time, the Valley of Screams
has connected

348
00:21:04,290 --> 00:21:08,454
the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

349
00:21:08,961 --> 00:21:10,861
Is it that unnatural?

350
00:21:11,363 --> 00:21:15,527
There's no way a tunnel connecting
two stars can be created natually!

351
00:21:16,102 --> 00:21:17,364
This is the same thing!

352
00:21:18,037 --> 00:21:20,505
There's no doubt that someone
is doing this deliberately.

353
00:21:21,307 --> 00:21:23,241
Hey! Speaking of which!

354
00:21:25,144 --> 00:21:26,509
Huh? What is it?

355
00:21:27,113 --> 00:21:31,049
There were some guys wearing
strange armor with those white monsters!

356
00:21:31,183 --> 00:21:32,343
I saw it!

357
00:21:32,852 --> 00:21:33,716
Armor?

358
00:21:33,819 --> 00:21:36,583
Do you remember it in more detail?

359
00:21:36,689 --> 00:21:38,816
Of course, I remember!

360
00:21:39,925 --> 00:21:42,393
Uhh... now let's see.

361
00:21:43,929 --> 00:21:46,363
I remember... I mean...

362
00:21:49,101 --> 00:21:51,535
Let me analyze this.

363
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:52,864
Yes, please do.

364
00:21:53,939 --> 00:21:57,109
Anyway, if this is being
done intentionally,

365
00:21:57,109 --> 00:21:58,633
then it is done with a grudge.

366
00:21:58,744 --> 00:21:59,938
What do they want?

367
00:22:00,212 --> 00:22:03,238
Well, I don't know. It's just...

368
00:22:03,782 --> 00:22:05,918
I have this feeling...

369
00:22:05,918 --> 00:22:08,888
that they're looking for
the Shinenju that has returned

370
00:22:08,888 --> 00:22:10,753
to the World of the Living.

371
00:22:11,957 --> 00:22:13,356
That's my hunch.

372
00:22:16,395 --> 00:22:19,159
We'll try to identify the enemy.

373
00:22:19,632 --> 00:22:21,793
Kurosaki, please keep
watch over the town.

374
00:22:22,334 --> 00:22:25,030
They are bound to appear again.

375
00:22:25,938 --> 00:22:28,429
And, if possible... find the Shinenju.

376
00:22:29,909 --> 00:22:31,343
Yeah, but...

377
00:22:31,343 --> 00:22:33,174
I still have to find that girl, too...

378
00:22:33,879 --> 00:22:34,709
Oh, sorry!

379
00:22:45,891 --> 00:22:47,483
What should I do?

380
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,053
Wow! You really came back?!

381
00:22:50,863 --> 00:22:52,455
Over here! Over here!

382
00:22:59,438 --> 00:23:02,498
Of course! I still have questions
I wanna ask.

383
00:23:02,641 --> 00:23:05,337
Fine! Let's pick up where we left off!
You're it!

384
00:23:06,312 --> 00:23:08,177
Hey, listen!

385
00:23:11,650 --> 00:23:12,674
That little...!

386
00:23:21,627 --> 00:23:23,862
All right... here goes with
the legendary performance!

387
00:23:23,862 --> 00:23:25,625
Take a deep breath...!

388
00:23:26,332 --> 00:23:28,459
Ready, and go!

389
00:23:28,701 --> 00:23:30,669
Ten, nine, eight, seven, six,
five, four, three, two, one!

390
00:23:30,736 --> 00:23:32,931
- It's all gone!
- Well done!

391
00:23:33,072 --> 00:23:34,198
Wasn't that too fast?!

392
00:23:34,340 --> 00:23:36,433
No such thing. It's good!

393
00:23:36,942 --> 00:23:38,967
All...

394
00:23:39,812 --> 00:23:40,710
right!

395
00:23:56,629 --> 00:23:57,960
Over there! Up there!

396
00:23:58,597 --> 00:23:59,393
Senna...!

397
00:24:00,099 --> 00:24:00,827
Hey...

398
00:24:01,233 --> 00:24:02,530
- What's that?
- Huh?!

399
00:24:05,271 --> 00:24:06,670
What's she doing?

400
00:24:06,872 --> 00:24:08,100
Is it some kind of act?

401
00:24:28,027 --> 00:24:29,426
This feels so nice.

402
00:24:47,746 --> 00:24:48,906
Where'd she go?

403
00:24:49,014 --> 00:24:50,413
She disappeared!

404
00:24:50,683 --> 00:24:51,945
No, in the back!

405
00:24:53,719 --> 00:24:55,277
Yay!

406
00:24:56,121 --> 00:24:57,452
Yay!

407
00:24:59,124 --> 00:25:00,648
- How was that, everyone?!
- Uh... hi.

408
00:25:02,361 --> 00:25:03,555
C'mon, join me!

409
00:25:03,595 --> 00:25:05,358
Err... Later.

410
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,360
No fair, they're getting
more attention than us!

411
00:25:12,838 --> 00:25:14,601
Thanks for the meal!

412
00:25:17,810 --> 00:25:19,311
You should've just told me.

413
00:25:19,311 --> 00:25:22,041
If you'd said you were treating,
I'd have answered anything!

414
00:25:23,182 --> 00:25:25,673
You didn't have any money?

415
00:25:27,686 --> 00:25:29,313
So what about it?

416
00:25:29,488 --> 00:25:30,921
What about what?

417
00:25:31,190 --> 00:25:32,851
I just explained it to you.

418
00:25:33,492 --> 00:25:37,428
Is there anything you know about
the Blanks and the Shinenju?

419
00:25:37,696 --> 00:25:38,993
Nope, I don't know anything.

420
00:25:39,064 --> 00:25:40,395
It's the first I've heard of them.

421
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:44,730
So someone used
those pointy-hat things to...

422
00:25:45,270 --> 00:25:47,261
what was it again?

423
00:25:47,539 --> 00:25:48,699
Shinenju.

424
00:25:48,841 --> 00:25:50,866
Look for that thing, right?

425
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:51,838
Yeah.

426
00:25:52,177 --> 00:25:53,610
So who is this someone?

427
00:25:54,179 --> 00:25:55,771
We're checking into that, too.

428
00:25:56,248 --> 00:25:57,510
For what?

429
00:25:58,150 --> 00:25:59,082
I dunno.

430
00:25:59,885 --> 00:26:02,046
Have you got any idea what
this Shinenju looks like?

431
00:26:03,288 --> 00:26:04,414
Not a clue.

432
00:26:05,157 --> 00:26:06,886
You're no help at all.

433
00:26:07,226 --> 00:26:11,720
You just have to wait until
the pointy hats appear again, right?

434
00:26:14,099 --> 00:26:16,124
Oh well, I'll help.

435
00:26:16,201 --> 00:26:16,997
Huh?

436
00:26:18,137 --> 00:26:19,968
But in return...

437
00:26:20,038 --> 00:26:21,164
I knew it!

438
00:26:21,607 --> 00:26:22,403
That!

439
00:26:22,541 --> 00:26:23,508
That?

440
00:26:23,742 --> 00:26:26,643
Take me for a ride on that and
I'll help you with whatever you want!

441
00:26:27,780 --> 00:26:29,543
I'm not fallin' for that again.

442
00:26:30,215 --> 00:26:31,239
Hey!

443
00:26:32,284 --> 00:26:34,616
You love heights, don't you?

444
00:26:34,953 --> 00:26:37,589
If you look at things from above,

445
00:26:37,589 --> 00:26:41,923
all the things that seem confusing
or messed up... suddenly become clear.

446
00:26:42,461 --> 00:26:44,156
Hey, that ribbon.

447
00:26:44,329 --> 00:26:48,663
Oh, you noticed?
Don't you think red is cuter?

448
00:26:48,801 --> 00:26:50,598
I don't mean that.
How'd you get it?

449
00:26:51,236 --> 00:26:55,036
I saw it in some shop and tried it on...

450
00:26:55,741 --> 00:26:57,943
I was looking at other things,
and forgot about it.

451
00:26:57,943 --> 00:26:59,069
It happens often, doesn't it?

452
00:26:59,178 --> 00:27:00,611
No way! Come with me!

453
00:27:01,513 --> 00:27:02,878
What about the tab here?

454
00:27:10,489 --> 00:27:11,547
I'd like to buy this.

455
00:27:12,458 --> 00:27:14,085
A present for your girlfriend?

456
00:27:14,693 --> 00:27:15,660
No!

457
00:27:15,928 --> 00:27:17,395
I'll gift wrap it for you.

458
00:27:17,996 --> 00:27:19,429
I'll take it as is!

459
00:27:21,467 --> 00:27:22,491
- Here.
- Oh...

460
00:27:23,802 --> 00:27:25,133
Thank you!

461
00:27:29,107 --> 00:27:29,971
Here.

462
00:27:30,409 --> 00:27:33,640
You're unexpectedly uptight,
actually going back to pay for it.

463
00:27:34,213 --> 00:27:37,512
Shut up! I hate that kind of thing.

464
00:27:38,016 --> 00:27:39,950
Thank you! What about
the Ferris wheel?

465
00:27:40,085 --> 00:27:41,575
Absolutely not.

466
00:27:41,653 --> 00:27:42,551
Meany!

467
00:27:42,721 --> 00:27:45,212
High-schoolers don't have
that much money.

468
00:27:47,292 --> 00:27:48,088
Hey!

469
00:27:48,293 --> 00:27:50,284
Shut up. I'm just going to the restroom!

470
00:28:01,306 --> 00:28:02,568
Okay...

471
00:28:04,409 --> 00:28:05,808
He's quite nice.

472
00:28:07,246 --> 00:28:08,873
There! All right!

473
00:28:20,926 --> 00:28:22,018
That river...

474
00:28:28,867 --> 00:28:30,698
Dad!

475
00:28:32,538 --> 00:28:33,766
Welcome home!

476
00:28:45,484 --> 00:28:46,678
Dad...?

477
00:28:49,521 --> 00:28:51,523
You were late tonight, huh?

478
00:28:51,523 --> 00:28:52,891
Mom, I'm hungry!

479
00:28:52,891 --> 00:28:54,483
I know. Take your seat.

480
00:28:54,927 --> 00:28:56,224
Okay then, cheers!

481
00:29:08,273 --> 00:29:10,002
What's taking so long?! Huh?

482
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:13,006
Huh?!

483
00:29:15,914 --> 00:29:17,848
This place was
so crowded a minute ago.

484
00:29:58,123 --> 00:30:00,751
This... is my...

485
00:30:05,297 --> 00:30:06,730
This is my funeral?

486
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,360
Dad? Mom?

487
00:30:19,711 --> 00:30:21,303
They are from earlier...

488
00:30:24,416 --> 00:30:25,144
What?!

489
00:30:29,788 --> 00:30:31,016
Now what?!

490
00:30:32,157 --> 00:30:34,557
You've got better reflexes
that I expected.

491
00:30:37,763 --> 00:30:39,162
What do you want with me?

492
00:30:39,831 --> 00:30:45,292
Come with us.
Our lord, Ganryu, summons you!

493
00:30:45,704 --> 00:30:48,468
Ganryu? Never heard of him.

494
00:30:49,041 --> 00:30:53,569
There's no need for you to know him,
since you are the...

495
00:30:53,679 --> 00:30:54,543
Jai!

496
00:30:56,148 --> 00:30:58,412
I told you not to blab.

497
00:30:59,651 --> 00:31:01,642
Jumping out like that...

498
00:31:04,122 --> 00:31:06,022
I'll catch her in an instant.

499
00:31:09,661 --> 00:31:11,856
Oh, that tickles.

500
00:31:19,538 --> 00:31:20,698
Don't crush her.

501
00:31:21,139 --> 00:31:23,107
Hurry it up. Let's go.

502
00:31:30,982 --> 00:31:32,973
Now then, let's go.

503
00:31:33,985 --> 00:31:34,849
Hold it!

504
00:31:36,388 --> 00:31:37,685
Where do you think you're going?

505
00:31:39,458 --> 00:31:41,483
You... Where did you come from?!

506
00:31:45,764 --> 00:31:48,096
My arm... my arm!

507
00:31:49,434 --> 00:31:51,129
What's with all the wandering off?

508
00:31:51,536 --> 00:31:52,503
Ichigo...

509
00:31:52,871 --> 00:31:54,065
That's my own business!

510
00:31:55,073 --> 00:31:58,270
No way.
You're gonna keep your promise.

511
00:31:59,845 --> 00:32:02,006
Hey, big guy. Sorry about that.

512
00:32:02,147 --> 00:32:04,672
You won't get away with this!
I won't let you!

513
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:06,479
Jai! Enough.

514
00:32:08,286 --> 00:32:10,345
It is not yet the time.

515
00:32:11,923 --> 00:32:14,221
Time? What're you talking about?

516
00:32:14,392 --> 00:32:15,324
Dammit!

517
00:32:16,194 --> 00:32:17,126
Hey, hold on!

518
00:32:20,699 --> 00:32:21,757
Hey!

519
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:24,834
You let someone treat you,
then run off?

520
00:32:24,870 --> 00:32:26,098
I didn't run away!

521
00:32:26,772 --> 00:32:27,636
Then what?

522
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:31,402
My family grave is here.

523
00:32:31,676 --> 00:32:33,303
Cut the crap.

524
00:32:33,712 --> 00:32:36,681
It's true. I remember it.

525
00:32:37,983 --> 00:32:40,679
It's hazy,
but I remember when I was alive.

526
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:43,485
That's why I came here for a look.

527
00:32:44,589 --> 00:32:46,216
My house used to be around here, too.

528
00:32:48,093 --> 00:32:51,688
I'll help you tomorrow for sure.
I'm not lying.

529
00:32:52,297 --> 00:32:52,991
See you!

530
00:32:53,665 --> 00:32:54,825
You idiot.

531
00:32:54,900 --> 00:32:57,528
Like I can abandon someone
who was just attacked.

532
00:33:02,841 --> 00:33:05,969
Bad guys are after her? That's fishy.

533
00:33:06,878 --> 00:33:08,280
Well, at any rate,

534
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,441
it's just for one night.

535
00:33:11,383 --> 00:33:12,475
I'm Senna.

536
00:33:13,151 --> 00:33:15,984
I'm Yuzu Kurosaki. Welcome.

537
00:33:16,221 --> 00:33:17,381
Thanks for having me.

538
00:33:17,689 --> 00:33:20,715
Hey Yuzu, let her sleep in your room.

539
00:33:21,159 --> 00:33:22,456
And let her bathe, too.

540
00:33:22,594 --> 00:33:23,754
- Bathe?!
- Okay.

541
00:33:29,067 --> 00:33:30,329
What's the matter, Dad?

542
00:33:31,102 --> 00:33:32,330
Hey! Yuzu, you too?

543
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:36,705
Come in until your bed's ready.

544
00:33:38,109 --> 00:33:41,272
Hmm... Boys' rooms are
always so drab and boring.

545
00:33:41,446 --> 00:33:42,378
Don't start.

546
00:33:45,083 --> 00:33:46,948
It seems like you've got
a nice family though.

547
00:33:47,052 --> 00:33:47,848
You think?

548
00:33:48,787 --> 00:33:50,448
My dad too. He was...

549
00:33:59,397 --> 00:33:59,954
Hey!

550
00:34:01,566 --> 00:34:02,362
Huh?

551
00:34:02,701 --> 00:34:03,668
What's the matter?

552
00:34:03,935 --> 00:34:06,403
Oh, nothing.

553
00:34:06,605 --> 00:34:09,733
By the way, why were
those guys after you?

554
00:34:10,208 --> 00:34:11,266
Did they say anything?

555
00:34:11,643 --> 00:34:16,774
Hmm... Something about Gan-whatever
wanted me brought to him.

556
00:34:17,082 --> 00:34:17,741
And?

557
00:34:17,883 --> 00:34:21,614
That's all. If you hadn't come by,
I might've learned more.

558
00:34:21,953 --> 00:34:22,977
What?!

559
00:34:23,221 --> 00:34:25,155
Hey, don't sleep in my bed!

560
00:34:25,257 --> 00:34:27,282
- Why? There's nothing wrong with it.
- Of course there is!

561
00:34:27,626 --> 00:34:28,684
Hey, don't lift your legs up!

562
00:34:28,727 --> 00:34:30,456
- You're such a bother!
- No, I'm not!

563
00:34:30,528 --> 00:34:32,018
Stop it!

564
00:34:32,130 --> 00:34:35,099
Shh! She says
she's gonna sleep in his bed!

565
00:34:35,133 --> 00:34:37,192
Well, Ichigo is a man, after all.

566
00:34:37,269 --> 00:34:38,069
Nooo!

567
00:34:38,069 --> 00:34:40,238
Oh, Masaki, it's the day
we've been dreading!

568
00:34:40,238 --> 00:34:42,035
What am I to do?

569
00:34:42,607 --> 00:34:45,007
Hey! What's goin' on out here?

570
00:34:45,176 --> 00:34:46,609
See, he's all mad.

571
00:34:46,678 --> 00:34:49,146
The bath is ready.

572
00:34:49,848 --> 00:34:51,042
Cripes!

573
00:34:52,584 --> 00:34:55,075
Hey Senna, take a bath
and then go to sleep.

574
00:34:56,254 --> 00:34:57,084
Hey!

575
00:35:08,633 --> 00:35:10,794
Kurosaki, it's me Urahara.

576
00:35:12,103 --> 00:35:14,833
Any leads on the Shinenju?

577
00:35:15,307 --> 00:35:20,142
Nope. But I encountered
the enemy Kon was talking about.

578
00:35:20,478 --> 00:35:21,342
Are you hurt?

579
00:35:21,813 --> 00:35:24,748
I'm fine. They took off right away.

580
00:35:25,650 --> 00:35:26,446
I see.

581
00:35:27,152 --> 00:35:30,849
About that, we were able to turn up
a few things up on our end.

582
00:35:31,222 --> 00:35:31,847
What?

583
00:35:32,557 --> 00:35:35,827
After analyzing the visual images
taken from Kon's memories...

584
00:35:35,827 --> 00:35:39,991
We identified the armor
as belonging to the clan

585
00:35:40,932 --> 00:35:44,803
that was banished long time ago
from the Soul Society

586
00:35:44,803 --> 00:35:47,135
after their take over attempt failed.

587
00:35:48,506 --> 00:35:52,272
So we know for sure that
they hold a grudge against us.

588
00:35:53,078 --> 00:35:56,013
But we still don't know
what they're after.

589
00:35:56,815 --> 00:35:59,648
Urahara, can I ask you one thing?

590
00:36:00,452 --> 00:36:01,510
What is it?

591
00:36:02,287 --> 00:36:07,122
Can a Soul Reaper have memories
of when they were alive?

592
00:36:08,159 --> 00:36:11,060
Let's see... I doubt that very much.

593
00:36:11,563 --> 00:36:13,190
Why do you ask?

594
00:36:14,866 --> 00:36:17,892
No reason... Just curious.

595
00:36:27,012 --> 00:36:29,708
Say, do you really think
they'll show up again?

596
00:36:30,015 --> 00:36:31,004
I dunno...

597
00:36:31,082 --> 00:36:35,314
But the only lead we have is
that we saw the Blanks here.

598
00:36:35,653 --> 00:36:37,280
Boring.

599
00:36:37,389 --> 00:36:39,857
Man, why so many people?

600
00:36:41,626 --> 00:36:44,493
It's usually less crowded around
this time of hour...

601
00:36:50,969 --> 00:36:53,597
Senna, don't go too far
from my side.

602
00:36:54,906 --> 00:36:55,873
Hey!

603
00:36:59,644 --> 00:37:00,736
Hey Senna!

604
00:37:00,845 --> 00:37:01,812
Over here!

605
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,847
Huh?

606
00:37:07,619 --> 00:37:11,885
You were just attacked yesterday!
Don't go wandering off like that!

607
00:37:14,793 --> 00:37:15,487
A soul?

608
00:37:17,929 --> 00:37:19,191
Hey, what's the matter?

609
00:37:21,599 --> 00:37:22,896
You're scaring him.

610
00:37:25,570 --> 00:37:28,630
My name's Senna. What's yours?

611
00:37:29,441 --> 00:37:30,465
Tomoya.

612
00:37:30,775 --> 00:37:32,003
Tomoya, huh?

613
00:37:32,510 --> 00:37:34,978
Will you tell me what's wrong?

614
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:39,976
Umm... My dad's gone...

615
00:37:40,885 --> 00:37:43,251
You were with your dad?

616
00:37:43,455 --> 00:37:47,692
Uh huh. We were driving to the festival,

617
00:37:47,692 --> 00:37:50,456
but when I looked,
he was gone.

618
00:37:50,695 --> 00:37:51,525
I see...

619
00:37:51,863 --> 00:37:52,887
Well then...

620
00:37:53,398 --> 00:37:56,834
Your dad is probably in heaven and...

621
00:37:57,202 --> 00:37:58,362
That's not true!

622
00:37:59,104 --> 00:38:01,163
Dad is looking for me!

623
00:38:01,706 --> 00:38:02,570
Okay!

624
00:38:02,841 --> 00:38:05,503
Then we'll help you find your dad.

625
00:38:05,710 --> 00:38:06,472
Really?

626
00:38:06,611 --> 00:38:08,010
Of course!

627
00:38:08,580 --> 00:38:10,571
Tomoya, which way
did you come from?

628
00:38:10,615 --> 00:38:11,479
Over that way!

629
00:38:11,583 --> 00:38:12,709
Then let's go.

630
00:38:12,784 --> 00:38:13,580
Hey!

631
00:38:14,319 --> 00:38:16,116
Hey! Right now, we have to...

632
00:38:16,187 --> 00:38:18,246
But we have no leads, right?

633
00:38:18,389 --> 00:38:20,823
No sense in hanging around here.
Let's go.

634
00:38:20,859 --> 00:38:21,553
Okay!

635
00:39:22,353 --> 00:39:24,344
Hey, how long're you gonna
keep at it?

636
00:39:25,924 --> 00:39:27,824
There's no festival around here.

637
00:39:29,694 --> 00:39:31,062
Besides...

638
00:39:31,062 --> 00:39:33,462
there's no guarantee that
his father is still on this side.

639
00:39:33,598 --> 00:39:34,565
We'll find him.

640
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:41,703
That boy has to leave this world soon.
And a long journey awaits him...

641
00:39:43,007 --> 00:39:47,273
It's his last wish.
How sad if it doesn't come true.

642
00:39:48,213 --> 00:39:51,080
I can't bring myself to perform
a Konso like this.

643
00:39:57,021 --> 00:39:58,283
I want to at least give him...

644
00:39:59,157 --> 00:40:01,523
a good last memory.

645
00:40:01,826 --> 00:40:03,259
Sis!

646
00:40:03,761 --> 00:40:04,750
What is it?

647
00:40:06,664 --> 00:40:09,098
Sis! This way! This way!

648
00:40:29,187 --> 00:40:31,883
Sis... My dad...

649
00:40:32,023 --> 00:40:34,355
Don't worry. Let's find him.

650
00:40:34,459 --> 00:40:35,426
Okay.

651
00:40:38,596 --> 00:40:40,689
I'm so glad this place is still here.

652
00:40:41,499 --> 00:40:43,467
I came here a lot as a child.

653
00:40:44,769 --> 00:40:45,599
You...

654
00:40:46,504 --> 00:40:47,368
Tomoya.

655
00:40:48,806 --> 00:40:49,966
Tomoya!

656
00:40:50,775 --> 00:40:51,833
Dad!

657
00:40:54,712 --> 00:40:55,679
Dad...

658
00:41:00,251 --> 00:41:02,811
I'm sorry... I'm so sorry.

659
00:41:07,058 --> 00:41:08,457
I don't believe this...

660
00:41:10,028 --> 00:41:11,256
Thank you so much!

661
00:41:11,529 --> 00:41:12,587
I'm happy for you.

662
00:41:12,764 --> 00:41:13,628
Uh huh.

663
00:41:15,500 --> 00:41:16,728
It's all thanks to you.

664
00:41:17,302 --> 00:41:20,135
No, I didn't do anything.

665
00:41:21,806 --> 00:41:26,709
I see. Could it be that
you haven't noticed?

666
00:41:27,412 --> 00:41:31,644
All these souls gathered
around you here.

667
00:41:32,650 --> 00:41:36,347
I was able to find this place
thanks to them.

668
00:41:37,889 --> 00:41:39,447
These people...?

669
00:41:40,224 --> 00:41:43,489
Uh huh... all of them here.

670
00:41:44,262 --> 00:41:47,231
How weird. You're the one
who called them here.

671
00:41:47,699 --> 00:41:50,634
Tomoya...
now we can go on our journey.

672
00:41:51,269 --> 00:41:52,395
Bye bye.

673
00:41:55,073 --> 00:41:55,767
Hey!

674
00:42:03,848 --> 00:42:05,713
Hey! Wait a minute.

675
00:42:08,986 --> 00:42:09,816
These guys...?!

676
00:42:14,692 --> 00:42:15,624
Why...

677
00:42:20,264 --> 00:42:22,528
Why do they come around me?

678
00:42:28,806 --> 00:42:32,902
Ichigo... I'm actually...

679
00:42:34,379 --> 00:42:35,277
I'm...

680
00:42:38,383 --> 00:42:39,315
Senna...

681
00:42:52,363 --> 00:42:53,489
Ukitake?

682
00:42:54,298 --> 00:42:55,287
What's wrong?

683
00:42:57,101 --> 00:42:59,092
What happened, Rukia?

684
00:42:59,737 --> 00:43:00,601
Well...

685
00:43:02,173 --> 00:43:05,631
This is a Level
One order from Central 46.

686
00:43:05,910 --> 00:43:08,071
Ichigo, hand over that girl!

687
00:43:08,246 --> 00:43:08,974
What?!

688
00:43:09,881 --> 00:43:13,751
Ichigo, I went through every record of
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads,

689
00:43:13,751 --> 00:43:18,279
the Stealth Force, the Kido Force,
and the Soul Reaper Academy...

690
00:43:18,689 --> 00:43:20,452
There is no Senna listed anywhere!

691
00:43:21,692 --> 00:43:25,263
And the zanpaku-to
the girl uses, Mirokumaru...

692
00:43:25,263 --> 00:43:28,166
It has been verified that it was
swallowed up by the Restrictive Current

693
00:43:28,166 --> 00:43:30,532
in the Dangai Precipice World
100 years ago along with its owner.

694
00:43:31,702 --> 00:43:35,331
In other words,
it cannot possibly exist today.

695
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:38,941
Wait a minute!
What are you saying?

696
00:43:39,911 --> 00:43:41,640
I'm a Soul Reaper...

697
00:43:41,879 --> 00:43:44,780
Then when did you come to
the World of the Living?

698
00:43:45,450 --> 00:43:50,478
Well... two days ago I woke up
by the banks of that river.

699
00:43:50,855 --> 00:43:53,653
But I remember my own name clearly.

700
00:43:54,425 --> 00:43:57,519
And that river...
I've known it since I was a child...

701
00:43:58,563 --> 00:43:59,825
But... why?

702
00:44:00,832 --> 00:44:02,766
I'm supposed to be just me...

703
00:44:03,034 --> 00:44:06,492
See? All kinds of memories are
mixed up in your head, right?

704
00:44:07,538 --> 00:44:09,403
It's hard to believe...

705
00:44:09,974 --> 00:44:13,740
But the collective of memories
you are searching for, the Shinenju,

706
00:44:14,045 --> 00:44:14,943
is you.

707
00:44:17,882 --> 00:44:18,906
I'm...

708
00:44:19,984 --> 00:44:22,646
The Valley of Screams became
visible twenty four hours ago...

709
00:44:23,321 --> 00:44:25,890
Soul Society has concluded that
the man behind it is Ganryu

710
00:44:25,890 --> 00:44:27,758
and his motive is to destroy the worlds...

711
00:44:27,758 --> 00:44:32,218
and that a crucial element
in his plans is the Shinenju.

712
00:44:33,531 --> 00:44:34,759
The Shinenju Senna!

713
00:44:36,534 --> 00:44:40,026
Soul Society will now take
you into custody!

714
00:44:42,440 --> 00:44:45,432
That's ridiculous?!
What are you saying?

715
00:44:46,310 --> 00:44:47,402
I'm...

716
00:44:48,079 --> 00:44:49,512
Even I'm!

717
00:44:49,747 --> 00:44:50,509
I...!

718
00:44:50,982 --> 00:44:53,712
Hold it. It just doesn't
sit well with me.

719
00:44:54,151 --> 00:44:56,016
Ichigo, what are you?!

720
00:44:57,021 --> 00:44:59,090
No matter what this girl is,

721
00:44:59,090 --> 00:45:01,183
it doesn't change the fact that
she exists at this moment.

722
00:45:01,726 --> 00:45:04,228
She gets mad, she gets happy,
she gets hurt...

723
00:45:04,228 --> 00:45:05,752
she has feelings, doesn't she?

724
00:45:06,898 --> 00:45:09,025
But you're gonna ignore that
and take her into custody?!

725
00:45:09,834 --> 00:45:12,302
Then you're no different from them!

726
00:45:13,771 --> 00:45:16,103
I'm not handing Senna over to you.

727
00:45:17,241 --> 00:45:20,438
Sorry, but this is not the time to debate.

728
00:45:20,745 --> 00:45:22,406
Move, Ichigo!

729
00:45:24,081 --> 00:45:25,378
Can't do that.

730
00:45:30,087 --> 00:45:31,452
What's that?!

731
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:43,796
Renji!

732
00:45:44,802 --> 00:45:45,564
Matsumoto!

733
00:46:00,251 --> 00:46:02,242
These guys!

734
00:46:03,521 --> 00:46:04,453
Behind you!

735
00:46:11,062 --> 00:46:15,260
Hey kid... Today, you will turn
the Shinenju over to us.

736
00:46:16,434 --> 00:46:19,562
Hah! You wanna lose
your other arm too?!

737
00:46:20,037 --> 00:46:20,867
Ichigo!

738
00:46:21,072 --> 00:46:22,562
- Kon, take care of her!
- Right!

739
00:46:36,587 --> 00:46:38,987
He has much more power
than yesterday!

740
00:46:45,262 --> 00:46:46,559
Protect the Shinenju!

741
00:46:47,031 --> 00:46:47,622
Yes ma'am!

742
00:46:50,067 --> 00:46:51,466
What are these things?!

743
00:46:52,903 --> 00:46:55,963
Reign over the frosted heavens!
Hyorinmaru!

744
00:47:07,318 --> 00:47:09,752
Roar! Zabimaru!

745
00:47:11,322 --> 00:47:12,311
What?!

746
00:47:16,727 --> 00:47:18,024
Sogyonokotowari!

747
00:47:18,796 --> 00:47:20,354
- Go, Kuchiki!
- Yes, sir!

748
00:47:20,665 --> 00:47:22,257
Get outta the way!

749
00:47:23,801 --> 00:47:24,859
Sis!

750
00:47:25,236 --> 00:47:27,329
Hado 33: Sokatsui!

751
00:47:28,272 --> 00:47:29,170
You're in my way!

752
00:47:30,441 --> 00:47:30,964
Hey!

753
00:47:31,842 --> 00:47:34,003
I am a Soul Reaper!

754
00:47:40,418 --> 00:47:41,942
Bring them to the twilight!

755
00:47:42,820 --> 00:47:43,684
Don't!

756
00:47:43,788 --> 00:47:44,914
Mirokumaru!

757
00:47:55,032 --> 00:47:55,862
Senna!

758
00:47:59,837 --> 00:48:01,236
As I suspected.

759
00:48:02,106 --> 00:48:04,442
That pattern on the armor belongs
to the banished clan...

760
00:48:04,442 --> 00:48:06,171
The once noble House of Ryodoji!

761
00:48:07,144 --> 00:48:08,475
I wouldn't know.

762
00:48:09,847 --> 00:48:13,044
We are from the Clan of Darkness,
the Dark One.

763
00:48:14,452 --> 00:48:15,510
What?!

764
00:48:16,387 --> 00:48:17,285
You won't get away!

765
00:48:32,436 --> 00:48:33,403
Let's go.

766
00:48:44,749 --> 00:48:46,478
You've got some nerve!

767
00:48:49,620 --> 00:48:50,814
Hey, let go of me!

768
00:48:51,288 --> 00:48:52,084
Senna!

769
00:48:53,758 --> 00:48:54,725
I'm coming for you!

770
00:49:01,732 --> 00:49:03,962
I won't hand Senna over!

771
00:49:10,241 --> 00:49:11,071
You're mine...!

772
00:49:19,216 --> 00:49:22,014
Ichigo? Ichigo!

773
00:49:31,495 --> 00:49:32,689
Ichigo!

774
00:49:35,266 --> 00:49:36,927
Nooo!

775
00:49:42,706 --> 00:49:43,604
Ichigo!

776
00:49:46,510 --> 00:49:47,272
Ichigo!

777
00:50:07,798 --> 00:50:08,765
He's okay now.

778
00:50:09,900 --> 00:50:12,664
Thank you.
I'm glad you all came to help.

779
00:50:12,970 --> 00:50:14,835
Sheesh, he's hopeless.

780
00:50:15,773 --> 00:50:17,172
No such thing.

781
00:50:17,875 --> 00:50:19,243
It was a surprise attack,

782
00:50:19,243 --> 00:50:22,269
but still there were three squad captains
and even they couldn't fend them off.

783
00:50:23,180 --> 00:50:24,112
It couldn't be helped.

784
00:50:24,348 --> 00:50:25,280
Boss...

785
00:50:25,416 --> 00:50:26,508
What about the squad members?

786
00:50:26,984 --> 00:50:30,044
Unfortunately, they lost track
of the enemy.

787
00:50:33,023 --> 00:50:34,888
Have you been able to learn
anything else?

788
00:50:34,992 --> 00:50:37,695
Yes, it seems they plan to use
the power of the Shinenju

789
00:50:37,695 --> 00:50:41,966
to pull the World of the Living
and the Soul Society together

790
00:50:41,966 --> 00:50:43,831
to make them collide.

791
00:50:45,135 --> 00:50:46,227
No way!

792
00:50:46,670 --> 00:50:50,663
It's hard to believe.
But that's the only explanation.

793
00:50:51,175 --> 00:50:52,472
What about the Soul Society?

794
00:50:52,910 --> 00:50:57,279
They should be working on
the next plan of action. Just...

795
00:50:57,715 --> 00:51:00,217
It's not possible to access
the Valley of Screams

796
00:51:00,217 --> 00:51:01,650
from the Soul Society.

797
00:51:02,586 --> 00:51:05,783
Without an entryway,
it's impossible to enter another world.

798
00:51:06,924 --> 00:51:08,084
Isn't there any other way?

799
00:51:09,093 --> 00:51:12,029
Well, there should be an entrance
in the World of the Living,

800
00:51:12,029 --> 00:51:15,931
which was created
when the Shinenju appeared.

801
00:51:16,367 --> 00:51:17,061
I see.

802
00:51:18,335 --> 00:51:19,063
Ichigo!

803
00:51:20,304 --> 00:51:22,966
If we find the entrance,
we can go after them.

804
00:51:25,476 --> 00:51:27,137
Right, Urahara?

805
00:51:28,412 --> 00:51:29,344
Yes.

806
00:51:30,547 --> 00:51:31,445
Let's go!

807
00:51:33,851 --> 00:51:34,613
Ichigo!

808
00:51:37,254 --> 00:51:39,814
We have no choice.
Let's go and search, too.

809
00:51:40,024 --> 00:51:40,854
- Right!
- Yes!

810
00:51:46,096 --> 00:51:47,531
As for the cause of the explosion,

811
00:51:47,531 --> 00:51:50,091
there are no traces of any gunpowder
or chemical residue.

812
00:51:50,467 --> 00:51:52,401
Hmmm...
What is going on here?!

813
00:52:17,227 --> 00:52:19,161
Ichigo... I...

814
00:52:19,930 --> 00:52:22,922
It's not your fault.

815
00:52:25,035 --> 00:52:28,402
She's self centered and stubborn
and a little crazy...

816
00:52:30,774 --> 00:52:31,900
But she was trembling.

817
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:39,283
Deep down, she was frightened...

818
00:52:39,283 --> 00:52:41,012
that she didn't know who
she really was.

819
00:52:44,288 --> 00:52:45,482
And yet...

820
00:52:47,558 --> 00:52:49,025
And yet, I couldn't protect her.

821
00:52:51,695 --> 00:52:56,325
Oh, you noticed?
Don't you think red is cuter?

822
00:52:57,267 --> 00:52:59,336
Remember when you told me that
if I answered your questions,

823
00:52:59,336 --> 00:53:01,702
you'd do anything I asked you to?

824
00:53:02,406 --> 00:53:04,775
If you look at things from above,

825
00:53:04,775 --> 00:53:07,544
all the things that seem confusing
or messed up...

826
00:53:07,544 --> 00:53:08,875
suddenly become clear.

827
00:53:10,814 --> 00:53:13,612
Why'd she say that...?

828
00:53:18,222 --> 00:53:19,814
Ichigo, what's wrong?

829
00:53:20,157 --> 00:53:21,852
Rukia, come with me.

830
00:53:22,059 --> 00:53:22,821
O Okay.

831
00:53:52,056 --> 00:53:55,617
I remember when I was alive.

832
00:53:56,660 --> 00:53:58,184
My house used to be
around here, too.

833
00:53:59,530 --> 00:54:01,760
There... in the river.

834
00:54:16,380 --> 00:54:17,278
What is that?!

835
00:54:21,685 --> 00:54:25,644
This is the same phenomenon
that's visible from the Soul Society!

836
00:54:26,390 --> 00:54:27,288
We can go through it!

837
00:54:27,925 --> 00:54:30,416
Rukia, contact Urahara.

838
00:54:30,727 --> 00:54:33,093
W Wait, Ichigo! You can't go alone...

839
00:54:33,197 --> 00:54:34,061
I'm going!

840
00:54:35,799 --> 00:54:37,391
I'm gonna...

841
00:54:37,935 --> 00:54:39,300
save her no matter what!

842
00:54:39,803 --> 00:54:40,462
Ichigo!

843
00:55:37,794 --> 00:55:38,988
What is this place...?

844
00:55:39,396 --> 00:55:42,194
I thought you wanted me to do
something for you!

845
00:55:43,033 --> 00:55:45,769
There's nothing for you to do.
We just need you...

846
00:55:45,769 --> 00:55:48,533
to be the instrument through
which we fulfill our dream.

847
00:55:49,006 --> 00:55:50,337
What are you talking about?!

848
00:55:50,474 --> 00:55:52,066
Lower your voice!

849
00:55:52,442 --> 00:55:57,072
Lord Ganryu is the rightful ruler
of Soul Society!

850
00:55:57,814 --> 00:56:01,250
It's all right. I abandoned
such formalities long ago.

851
00:56:02,819 --> 00:56:05,656
One thousand years have passed
since my grandfather

852
00:56:05,656 --> 00:56:08,716
gave in to the unjust laws
and was banished from Soul Society.

853
00:56:09,126 --> 00:56:13,230
We wandered in exile in
this Dangai Precipice World...

854
00:56:13,230 --> 00:56:16,133
and survived by evading
the Restrictive Current,

855
00:56:16,133 --> 00:56:18,158
which swallows up everything
that touches it.

856
00:56:20,204 --> 00:56:21,772
We learned a way to utilize the souls

857
00:56:21,772 --> 00:56:24,007
who had strayed from
the Cycle of Transmigration

858
00:56:24,007 --> 00:56:28,111
and turned into wandering ghosts
in the Dangai Precipice World

859
00:56:28,111 --> 00:56:31,877
as a source of power.

860
00:56:35,686 --> 00:56:38,120
The number of souls is
always constant.

861
00:56:41,091 --> 00:56:45,429
Therefore, when these souls,
or "Blanks" who have strayed

862
00:56:45,429 --> 00:56:47,664
from the Cycle of
Transmigration reach a certain number...

863
00:56:47,664 --> 00:56:51,001
they're naturally drawn together
and generate a dimension

864
00:56:51,001 --> 00:56:52,969
known as the Valley of Screams.

865
00:56:53,270 --> 00:56:57,730
In other words, this space was
created by countless Blanks.

866
00:56:58,275 --> 00:56:59,509
And at the same time,

867
00:56:59,509 --> 00:57:03,146
all the memories of these lost souls
merge into one object

868
00:57:03,146 --> 00:57:04,704
and return to
the World of the Living.

869
00:57:05,215 --> 00:57:06,739
That is the Shinenju...

870
00:57:06,883 --> 00:57:08,578
In other words... you!

871
00:57:09,786 --> 00:57:13,313
However, the Blanks do not lose
their individuality right away.

872
00:57:13,991 --> 00:57:15,592
Even though the Blanks
are basically empty vessels,

873
00:57:15,592 --> 00:57:19,858
they still wander for a time,
searching for their memories.

874
00:57:26,470 --> 00:57:28,267
This is where the problem begins.

875
00:57:29,139 --> 00:57:32,109
Placing the Shinenju at
the center of the Valley of Screams

876
00:57:32,109 --> 00:57:35,746
will activate the Blanks' natural desire
to seek their memories...

877
00:57:35,746 --> 00:57:38,615
and will drive them to
rush towards the Shinenju,

878
00:57:38,615 --> 00:57:41,083
causing the Valley of Screams
to contract.

879
00:57:41,852 --> 00:57:45,489
This force will be strong enough
to pull the World of the Living

880
00:57:45,489 --> 00:57:48,191
and Soul Society, which is separated
by the Dangai Precipice World,

881
00:57:48,191 --> 00:57:50,182
into a collision.

882
00:57:50,694 --> 00:57:51,683
What?!

883
00:57:52,529 --> 00:57:54,929
That's a disturbing thought...

884
00:57:55,966 --> 00:57:59,094
Furthermore, the contraction
has already begun.

885
00:57:59,403 --> 00:58:01,098
Never mind all the details.

886
00:58:01,405 --> 00:58:03,737
So what's going to happen?

887
00:58:04,374 --> 00:58:05,398
Who knows...?

888
00:58:05,742 --> 00:58:08,812
But two world that must stay apart
are going to collide.

889
00:58:08,812 --> 00:58:10,871
One will be destroyed if we are lucky.

890
00:58:11,014 --> 00:58:13,915
Perhaps, both world will be destroyed.

891
00:58:14,151 --> 00:58:16,881
How much time do we have?

892
00:58:17,354 --> 00:58:20,221
I don't have enough data,
so I can't say with certainty...

893
00:58:20,624 --> 00:58:22,990
Bu I'd guess... about one hour.

894
00:58:24,227 --> 00:58:27,162
I'll mobilize the Punishment Force and
enter the Valley of Screams immediately!

895
00:58:27,597 --> 00:58:28,859
It's useless.

896
00:58:29,499 --> 00:58:31,468
There is no Senkaimon that connects

897
00:58:31,468 --> 00:58:33,837
the Soul Society to
the Valley of Screams,

898
00:58:33,837 --> 00:58:36,362
therefore we have no way to enter.

899
00:58:37,040 --> 00:58:39,235
Any effort will be for naught.

900
00:58:40,911 --> 00:58:44,847
The situation is critical!
Prepare the Kido Cannon!

901
00:58:45,349 --> 00:58:50,412
We must destroy the Valley of Screams
and the entire dimension connected to it.

902
00:58:50,554 --> 00:58:54,923
But if we do that, it will cause
massive damage to the both worlds!

903
00:58:55,926 --> 00:58:58,087
There is no other choice.

904
00:59:01,231 --> 00:59:02,892
No! Please stand back!

905
00:59:08,605 --> 00:59:11,574
What is the meaning of this?!
This is a captains' meeting!

906
00:59:12,008 --> 00:59:12,770
Be gone!

907
00:59:14,544 --> 00:59:15,943
My deepest apologies, sir!

908
00:59:16,313 --> 00:59:18,713
I will gladly accept any punishment later.

909
00:59:19,282 --> 00:59:22,581
However, I have crucial information
to report!

910
00:59:23,387 --> 00:59:25,489
The Substitute Soul Reaper,
Ichigo Kurosaki, has discovered

911
00:59:25,489 --> 00:59:28,558
an entryway to the Valley of Screams
through the World of the Living...

912
00:59:28,558 --> 00:59:31,994
and has gone there in order to rescue
Senna the Shinenju!

913
00:59:33,397 --> 00:59:34,261
I beseech you...

914
00:59:34,931 --> 00:59:37,525
Please send reinforcements
to assist Ichigo Kurosaki!

915
00:59:38,702 --> 00:59:40,863
Well... but...

916
00:59:42,906 --> 00:59:45,340
I cannot allow that.

917
00:59:45,442 --> 00:59:46,670
Why is that?

918
00:59:47,344 --> 00:59:51,075
Mind you, I am not taking
the Substitute Soul Reaper's skills lightly...

919
00:59:51,281 --> 00:59:53,717
However, we have only one hour,

920
00:59:53,717 --> 00:59:57,554
and there is no guarantee that
we could enter the Valley of Screams,

921
00:59:57,554 --> 00:59:59,890
defeat the enemy and rescue
the Shinenju in that time

922
00:59:59,890 --> 01:00:02,552
even with the full force of
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads.

923
01:00:03,627 --> 01:00:05,185
Do not think poorly of me.

924
01:00:05,996 --> 01:00:07,486
This meeting is now over.

925
01:00:07,998 --> 01:00:10,467
All Squads will begin
emergency procedures.

926
01:00:10,467 --> 01:00:12,401
Prepare the Kido Cannon!

927
01:00:50,607 --> 01:00:53,633
- I'm...
- I'm... going, too!

928
01:00:54,277 --> 01:00:56,871
I'm not about to let him
take all the glory.

929
01:01:19,870 --> 01:01:23,601
Lord Ganryu, the Blanks have
latched onto the Shinenju.

930
01:01:24,574 --> 01:01:25,404
Yes.

931
01:01:33,416 --> 01:01:34,849
Humph! A small fry, I see...

932
01:01:37,754 --> 01:01:39,153
Senna!

933
01:01:40,423 --> 01:01:41,617
I'm coming!

934
01:01:54,738 --> 01:01:56,706
Have you returned for
another beating?

935
01:01:57,107 --> 01:01:58,438
Give Senna back!

936
01:02:05,148 --> 01:02:09,312
Just when we were trying
to awaken her as Shinenju...

937
01:02:09,553 --> 01:02:10,854
Because of you,

938
01:02:10,854 --> 01:02:14,585
she will now suffer pain and
fear as a human being.

939
01:02:17,427 --> 01:02:18,325
Ichigo...

940
01:02:19,896 --> 01:02:20,828
What?!

941
01:02:21,565 --> 01:02:23,533
No... no!

942
01:02:23,667 --> 01:02:24,759
Senna!

943
01:02:28,738 --> 01:02:30,399
Nooo!

944
01:02:31,041 --> 01:02:32,269
You bastards!

945
01:02:32,542 --> 01:02:33,804
Get outta my way!

946
01:02:52,362 --> 01:02:56,025
Maybe we should all go after Kurosaki.

947
01:02:56,433 --> 01:02:57,730
You better not.

948
01:02:58,201 --> 01:03:01,500
The Valley of Screams is
somewhat similar to the Soul Society...

949
01:03:01,671 --> 01:03:04,504
It's a spiritual world
where humans cannot go.

950
01:03:07,777 --> 01:03:08,869
Hmm?

951
01:03:11,748 --> 01:03:12,737
Kuchiki?

952
01:03:13,516 --> 01:03:14,813
Abarai!

953
01:03:15,819 --> 01:03:16,808
How was it?

954
01:03:18,054 --> 01:03:19,112
No good.

955
01:03:19,322 --> 01:03:21,958
Soul Society intends to
use the Kido Cannon

956
01:03:21,958 --> 01:03:24,518
to destroy
the entire Valley of Screams.

957
01:03:24,661 --> 01:03:26,891
If they do that,
what'll happen to Kurosaki...?!

958
01:03:28,832 --> 01:03:30,732
I won't let that happen.

959
01:03:31,334 --> 01:03:35,600
Before they fire the Kido Cannon,
we'll go and finish the job.

960
01:03:36,306 --> 01:03:37,273
But...

961
01:03:37,941 --> 01:03:40,671
Don't worry. We'll figure something out.

962
01:03:40,810 --> 01:03:43,108
You wouldn't stand a chance
going in by yourselves.

963
01:03:44,881 --> 01:03:45,643
Oh!

964
01:03:46,049 --> 01:03:47,983
We've already put the team together.

965
01:03:48,518 --> 01:03:50,349
We'll settle this ourselves!

966
01:03:50,987 --> 01:03:52,420
I'm coming, too!

967
01:03:53,757 --> 01:03:55,850
There's no time. Let's go!

968
01:03:57,627 --> 01:03:58,594
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

969
01:03:59,295 --> 01:04:02,287
Kuchiki... Please take care of Kurosaki.

970
01:04:03,366 --> 01:04:04,390
I know.

971
01:04:32,195 --> 01:04:32,923
Let go!

972
01:04:40,737 --> 01:04:41,601
Dammit!

973
01:04:52,082 --> 01:04:52,946
Kenpachi!

974
01:04:53,383 --> 01:04:55,180
It's dangerous, over there.

975
01:05:01,791 --> 01:05:02,917
You too...!

976
01:05:04,260 --> 01:05:04,885
Huh?

977
01:05:07,230 --> 01:05:08,424
What was that?

978
01:05:18,641 --> 01:05:20,506
What's taking you so long?!

979
01:05:21,377 --> 01:05:22,309
You guys!

980
01:05:23,246 --> 01:05:25,840
You're not getting away with this...
coming all by yourself!

981
01:05:25,882 --> 01:05:29,682
Thought we'd join in for some fun.

982
01:05:30,787 --> 01:05:33,723
Look how many people
volunteered to the call.

983
01:05:33,723 --> 01:05:35,953
Leave this side to us!

984
01:05:36,493 --> 01:05:38,154
Now go, Kurosaki!

985
01:05:40,396 --> 01:05:41,420
I'm counting on you guys!

986
01:05:44,100 --> 01:05:45,294
- Let's do it!
- Right!

987
01:05:47,570 --> 01:05:50,664
Extend! Hozukimaru!

988
01:05:59,182 --> 01:06:00,649
Roar! Haineko!

989
01:06:11,294 --> 01:06:12,727
Raise your head!

990
01:06:12,962 --> 01:06:14,088
Wabisuke!

991
01:06:23,439 --> 01:06:25,202
Take that! You pesky brat!

992
01:06:36,152 --> 01:06:37,210
What's going on?!

993
01:06:37,720 --> 01:06:38,482
Hey!

994
01:06:41,558 --> 01:06:43,321
Is this what you're looking for?

995
01:06:45,195 --> 01:06:46,253
Why you!

996
01:07:04,747 --> 01:07:06,146
You little!

997
01:07:18,862 --> 01:07:21,160
It's too late! There!

998
01:07:44,821 --> 01:07:45,913
Ridiculous...

999
01:07:48,925 --> 01:07:49,755
What?!

1000
01:07:52,028 --> 01:07:55,088
I don't like playing tag,
but I'm not bad at it!

1001
01:07:59,736 --> 01:08:01,431
Go, Kenny!

1002
01:08:03,106 --> 01:08:04,698
Can I cut you already?

1003
01:08:05,141 --> 01:08:06,108
Dammit!

1004
01:08:10,246 --> 01:08:11,270
What do you know?

1005
01:08:11,814 --> 01:08:13,941
You might just turn out to
be some fun, after all.

1006
01:08:36,539 --> 01:08:40,339
Reign over the frosted heavens!
Hyorinmaru!

1007
01:08:51,154 --> 01:08:52,985
Hanging in there, huh, kid?

1008
01:08:53,256 --> 01:08:57,249
Let's see who'll last longer, shall we?

1009
01:08:57,427 --> 01:09:00,555
Well, I don't mind if this
keeps up forever.

1010
01:09:01,297 --> 01:09:02,161
Take this!

1011
01:09:33,963 --> 01:09:35,931
Humph... Looks like it's over

1012
01:09:45,208 --> 01:09:46,266
Bankai!

1013
01:09:47,076 --> 01:09:49,408
Daigurenhyorinmaru!

1014
01:09:50,213 --> 01:09:53,671
Dammit! I can't believe
he still has that kind of power left!

1015
01:09:55,184 --> 01:09:56,242
What's going on?!

1016
01:09:56,786 --> 01:09:57,514
What?!

1017
01:10:15,271 --> 01:10:16,795
Third chant complete.

1018
01:10:17,073 --> 01:10:18,802
We are ready to fire.

1019
01:10:21,010 --> 01:10:22,512
Research Technology
CommCenter reports

1020
01:10:22,512 --> 01:10:25,447
the target will pass out of
critical range in five minutes.

1021
01:10:29,419 --> 01:10:30,351
Head Captain!

1022
01:10:30,686 --> 01:10:32,119
I understand.

1023
01:10:32,422 --> 01:10:36,119
I will wait until the very last second.
However...

1024
01:10:45,835 --> 01:10:48,326
I said I won't let you get
to the Shinenju!

1025
01:10:52,675 --> 01:10:53,869
Ichigo, grab on!

1026
01:11:05,488 --> 01:11:06,284
What?!

1027
01:11:06,689 --> 01:11:07,485
Renji!

1028
01:11:07,657 --> 01:11:09,454
Go! Ichigo!

1029
01:11:12,462 --> 01:11:13,429
What?!

1030
01:11:15,465 --> 01:11:16,864
You're not going anywhere!

1031
01:11:21,070 --> 01:11:23,561
Then we'll finish you two first!

1032
01:11:34,717 --> 01:11:35,615
What?!

1033
01:11:49,599 --> 01:11:52,295
Senna!

1034
01:11:53,002 --> 01:11:56,494
You still believe you can
save the Shinenju?

1035
01:11:57,206 --> 01:12:00,369
Damn right!
I'm gonna save Senna!

1036
01:12:06,949 --> 01:12:08,177
It's too late!

1037
01:12:08,818 --> 01:12:12,811
The Shinenju has already begun
to merge with the Valley of Screams.

1038
01:12:13,222 --> 01:12:15,918
No one can stop it now.

1039
01:12:16,425 --> 01:12:18,985
Shaddup! You just wait, Senna!

1040
01:12:19,195 --> 01:12:21,129
I'll get you outta here real soon!

1041
01:12:21,831 --> 01:12:24,197
You still don't seem to understand.

1042
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:26,500
How useless it is.

1043
01:12:26,802 --> 01:12:28,963
Getsugatensho!

1044
01:12:34,243 --> 01:12:35,540
Why you!

1045
01:12:36,846 --> 01:12:38,609
So you finally showed yourself!

1046
01:12:39,649 --> 01:12:42,743
I'll beat you and save Senna!

1047
01:12:43,653 --> 01:12:45,120
Go ahead, bring it on!

1048
01:12:45,855 --> 01:12:46,719
Let's go!

1049
01:12:47,023 --> 01:12:49,048
Ban... kai!

1050
01:12:57,833 --> 01:12:59,198
Tensazangetsu!

1051
01:13:46,782 --> 01:13:49,485
For a millennium,
our clan was forced

1052
01:13:49,485 --> 01:13:54,184
to nest in the crevices of
the Dangai Precipice World in disgrace.

1053
01:13:55,057 --> 01:13:59,687
We were able to endure
that suffering until this day...

1054
01:14:00,129 --> 01:14:05,260
because of our hatred...
our desire to destroy Soul Society!

1055
01:14:05,635 --> 01:14:09,366
And that moment is about to happen!

1056
01:14:10,006 --> 01:14:12,065
I will not let you interfere!

1057
01:14:22,251 --> 01:14:24,719
Why are you so determined?

1058
01:14:25,087 --> 01:14:28,291
The Shinenju is just
a collective of memories.

1059
01:14:28,291 --> 01:14:30,987
A mere remains of what
used to be alive.

1060
01:14:32,662 --> 01:14:34,129
That's not true!

1061
01:14:34,864 --> 01:14:35,796
Senna is...

1062
01:14:36,332 --> 01:14:38,994
Senna is here and she's alive!

1063
01:14:45,041 --> 01:14:48,408
She was confused and afraid,
looking for help...

1064
01:14:49,412 --> 01:14:51,505
I'm going to protect her...

1065
01:14:53,282 --> 01:14:56,649
I swore it on my soul!

1066
01:15:17,239 --> 01:15:18,399
I get it now...

1067
01:15:19,241 --> 01:15:22,836
All of you are just...

1068
01:15:23,279 --> 01:15:25,372
Ichigo!

1069
01:15:35,691 --> 01:15:37,784
We pass out of critical range
in two minutes!

1070
01:15:38,160 --> 01:15:40,594
No word yet?
What are they doing?!

1071
01:15:42,598 --> 01:15:45,260
I can wait no longer!

1072
01:15:46,035 --> 01:15:47,024
Sensei!

1073
01:15:49,672 --> 01:15:52,232
Fire the Kido Cannon!

1074
01:16:19,769 --> 01:16:20,531
Captain!

1075
01:16:20,836 --> 01:16:23,862
The cannon's been fired!
The entire dimension will collapse!

1076
01:16:31,480 --> 01:16:32,378
What?!

1077
01:16:37,052 --> 01:16:39,384
My zanpaku to is pretty tough.

1078
01:16:39,922 --> 01:16:43,289
That kind of attack
won't change a thing!

1079
01:16:54,937 --> 01:16:56,461
You're not getting away!

1080
01:16:57,206 --> 01:16:58,571
There's no need to run away!

1081
01:16:59,041 --> 01:16:59,837
You impudent!

1082
01:17:00,609 --> 01:17:03,544
Dance! Sodenoshirayuki!

1083
01:17:05,948 --> 01:17:07,176
It's useless!

1084
01:17:08,083 --> 01:17:09,345
Somenomai.

1085
01:17:11,287 --> 01:17:12,413
Tsukishiro!

1086
01:17:37,179 --> 01:17:38,077
What?!

1087
01:17:38,881 --> 01:17:41,111
Like I said, it's useless!

1088
01:17:41,283 --> 01:17:41,942
Take this!

1089
01:17:49,725 --> 01:17:50,692
Brother!

1090
01:17:53,996 --> 01:17:55,531
Be honored...

1091
01:17:55,531 --> 01:17:58,466
that you will perish by my Bankai.

1092
01:17:59,235 --> 01:18:01,999
Scatter! Senbonzakurakageyoshi.

1093
01:18:09,245 --> 01:18:10,109
Brother!

1094
01:18:10,980 --> 01:18:11,810
Let's go.

1095
01:18:16,752 --> 01:18:17,719
Senna!

1096
01:18:42,578 --> 01:18:43,545
Here I come!

1097
01:18:45,548 --> 01:18:46,515
Come on!

1098
01:19:23,485 --> 01:19:25,544
Hey, you're awfully quiet.

1099
01:19:26,355 --> 01:19:28,084
What's the matter,
cat got your tongue?

1100
01:19:34,730 --> 01:19:36,061
Shut up.

1101
01:19:45,574 --> 01:19:46,802
They're coming back.

1102
01:20:14,336 --> 01:20:16,167
They've successfully retrieved
the Shinenju!

1103
01:20:16,271 --> 01:20:18,205
The Valley of Screams
is disintegrating!

1104
01:20:47,236 --> 01:20:48,066
Welcome home!

1105
01:20:48,637 --> 01:20:49,661
Sis!

1106
01:20:50,939 --> 01:20:52,566
Kurosaki, you did it!

1107
01:20:53,976 --> 01:20:56,501
Well done. You did it!

1108
01:20:56,578 --> 01:20:57,340
Quite impressive.

1109
01:20:57,980 --> 01:20:59,914
I'm so glad everyone is all right.

1110
01:21:00,983 --> 01:21:03,315
Thanks! Rukia! Renji!

1111
01:21:03,819 --> 01:21:06,379
Stupid! We didn't do it for you.

1112
01:21:07,356 --> 01:21:10,257
I must admit,
not bad for the freeloader.

1113
01:21:10,392 --> 01:21:11,381
What?!

1114
01:21:11,460 --> 01:21:13,052
You can stay and eat.

1115
01:21:13,762 --> 01:21:16,128
Senna! I forgot, your ribbon...

1116
01:21:19,301 --> 01:21:20,199
Ichigo...

1117
01:21:28,977 --> 01:21:32,105
What is it?
Why won't the alarm stop?

1118
01:21:34,717 --> 01:21:35,784
It's no good!

1119
01:21:35,784 --> 01:21:38,309
The dimension passed beyond
the critical zone!

1120
01:21:38,487 --> 01:21:39,988
Gravity was created and is pulling

1121
01:21:39,988 --> 01:21:42,582
the World of the Living and the Soul Society
together on a collision course!

1122
01:21:43,058 --> 01:21:44,082
At this rate...!

1123
01:21:49,064 --> 01:21:50,258
What's going on?!

1124
01:21:51,133 --> 01:21:52,327
It's not stopping?!

1125
01:21:53,435 --> 01:21:54,959
Then what'll happen?

1126
01:21:55,604 --> 01:21:56,969
This is not good.

1127
01:21:58,440 --> 01:21:59,372
Wait!

1128
01:22:04,446 --> 01:22:05,435
Why?!

1129
01:22:10,419 --> 01:22:11,579
This is bad.

1130
01:22:11,820 --> 01:22:14,186
Dammit! Is it too late?

1131
01:22:33,075 --> 01:22:35,509
Ichigo... I'm scared.

1132
01:22:36,745 --> 01:22:37,575
Senna?

1133
01:22:38,447 --> 01:22:40,677
But... But...

1134
01:22:42,484 --> 01:22:43,610
I won't let it happen.

1135
01:22:43,986 --> 01:22:45,817
Not when it's such a wonderful world.

1136
01:22:47,089 --> 01:22:50,354
Not when...
so many people live in it.

1137
01:22:51,527 --> 01:22:52,551
Not when...

1138
01:22:54,930 --> 01:22:57,558
You live here, Ichigo...!

1139
01:23:02,204 --> 01:23:03,228
It's okay.

1140
01:23:03,806 --> 01:23:06,400
The Blanks are still near me.

1141
01:23:07,342 --> 01:23:10,072
If I release their energy all at once,

1142
01:23:10,679 --> 01:23:13,705
the two worlds can probably
be returned to normal.

1143
01:23:15,150 --> 01:23:16,014
Senna?!

1144
01:23:18,420 --> 01:23:22,151
If there's no world, you'll be gone, too...

1145
01:23:25,394 --> 01:23:27,191
I don't want that.

1146
01:23:32,034 --> 01:23:33,968
Stop! You still have...

1147
01:23:35,170 --> 01:23:38,833
I don't want you to die instead of me!

1148
01:23:42,578 --> 01:23:43,510
Senna...

1149
01:23:44,179 --> 01:23:45,737
Senna!

1150
01:23:53,021 --> 01:23:55,324
Countless explosions in
the Dangai Precipice World

1151
01:23:55,324 --> 01:23:56,558
have been confirmed!

1152
01:23:56,558 --> 01:23:58,193
The Soul Society and
the World of the Living

1153
01:23:58,193 --> 01:24:00,218
are both moving
towards their respective stable positions.

1154
01:24:01,396 --> 01:24:03,660
The collision has been averted!

1155
01:24:06,034 --> 01:24:08,935
Ichigo, I have a favor to ask.

1156
01:24:47,876 --> 01:24:51,209
I want you to check...
my family grave...

1157
01:24:52,948 --> 01:24:56,384
Remember yesterday,
I told you it was here?

1158
01:24:58,253 --> 01:25:02,053
I was alive once for sure...
and I lived in this town...

1159
01:25:03,125 --> 01:25:03,955
So...

1160
01:25:04,393 --> 01:25:05,018
Yeah.

1161
01:25:07,095 --> 01:25:11,361
I must've had a family.

1162
01:25:14,102 --> 01:25:16,070
I existed.

1163
01:25:17,606 --> 01:25:21,064
So there should be
a name on the grave...

1164
01:25:25,414 --> 01:25:26,381
Was it around here?

1165
01:25:27,749 --> 01:25:29,944
The fourth one from the end.

1166
01:25:36,692 --> 01:25:38,592
Is there... a name?

1167
01:25:40,162 --> 01:25:43,154
My vision is blurred...

1168
01:25:51,306 --> 01:25:52,295
Is it there?

1169
01:25:54,676 --> 01:25:56,769
Yeah, it's here.

1170
01:26:00,115 --> 01:26:01,810
You lived in this town.

1171
01:26:03,118 --> 01:26:04,642
You had a family, too.

1172
01:26:11,360 --> 01:26:12,486
I'm glad...

1173
01:26:22,337 --> 01:26:23,531
It feels so warm.

1174
01:26:25,874 --> 01:26:29,105
We'll... meet again, won't we?

1175
01:26:29,778 --> 01:26:32,872
What're you saying?
Of course...

1176
01:27:09,017 --> 01:27:12,077
The Blanks' energy will
soon be depleted...

1177
01:27:13,822 --> 01:27:16,658
And everything about Senna...

1178
01:27:16,658 --> 01:27:18,956
will fade from our memories.

1179
01:27:19,928 --> 01:27:24,024
Memories of those that never existed
can't possibly remain...

1180
01:27:30,205 --> 01:27:33,697
I know she'll be gone soon,
but right now...

1181
01:27:34,409 --> 01:27:35,967
I can still hear her voice.

1182
01:27:49,991 --> 01:27:53,228
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1183
01:27:53,228 --> 01:27:56,459
repeating and wandering through

1184
01:27:56,665 --> 01:28:01,069
The single answer I've found is

1185
01:28:01,069 --> 01:28:07,075
no matter how scared, or hurt I become,

1186
01:28:07,075 --> 01:28:11,011
I tell the person I love, "I love you"

1187
01:28:33,368 --> 01:28:39,841
I don't care whether you
"do love me, or do not love me"

1188
01:28:39,841 --> 01:28:45,013
In this world, there are way too many
things that cannot be changed,

1189
01:28:45,013 --> 01:28:47,048
no matter how hard you wish

1190
01:28:47,048 --> 01:28:50,719
And the fact that I love you

1191
01:28:50,719 --> 01:28:56,487
Is the truth that cannot
be changed by anyone

1192
01:28:59,528 --> 01:29:02,397
Crossing over a thousand nights,

1193
01:29:02,397 --> 01:29:09,428
I want to tell you,
I have to tell you

1194
01:29:09,538 --> 01:29:12,207
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1195
01:29:12,207 --> 01:29:15,644
repeating and wandering

1196
01:29:15,644 --> 01:29:20,115
The single answer I've found is

1197
01:29:20,115 --> 01:29:26,145
no matter how scared, or hurt I become,

1198
01:29:26,254 --> 01:29:30,247
I tell the person I love, "I love you"

1199
01:29:30,992 --> 01:29:36,665
It is scary to put feelings into words,

1200
01:29:36,665 --> 01:29:42,262
but I'll tell the person I love,
"I love you"

1201
01:29:52,981 --> 01:29:55,584
There is no way to express in words,

1202
01:29:55,584 --> 01:29:59,179
the joy of coming across each other
in this vast world

1203
01:29:59,287 --> 01:30:02,023
That is why we smile,

1204
01:30:02,023 --> 01:30:05,427
singing the passing colorful autumn
in sol fa,

1205
01:30:05,427 --> 01:30:08,191
facing back against the winter,

1206
01:30:08,330 --> 01:30:11,466
waiting for the spring sunlight
through the trees,

1207
01:30:11,466 --> 01:30:15,800
in order to be reborn
So that we can protect someone

1208
01:30:16,037 --> 01:30:18,573
The path I came, and the path I go,

1209
01:30:18,573 --> 01:30:25,638
whenever I turn back
I had cowardly eyes

1210
01:30:25,814 --> 01:30:28,749
I want to face it,
but cannot be honest about it.

1211
01:30:28,783 --> 01:30:34,389
Repeating over the days of
not being able to love the person

1212
01:30:34,389 --> 01:30:40,562
But hating to be by myself,

1213
01:30:40,562 --> 01:30:46,558
I tried to love someone without getting hurt

1214
01:31:13,161 --> 01:31:15,697
Crossing over a thousand nights,

1215
01:31:15,697 --> 01:31:23,035
I shall go to you now,
there is something I must tell you.

1216
01:31:23,238 --> 01:31:25,940
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1217
01:31:25,940 --> 01:31:29,103
repeating and wandering

1218
01:31:29,277 --> 01:31:33,715
The single answer I've found is

1219
01:31:33,715 --> 01:31:39,721
no matter how scared,
or hurt I become,

1220
01:31:39,721 --> 01:31:44,124
I tell the person I love, "I love you"

1221
01:31:44,559 --> 01:31:50,498
Even if that feeling is denied,

1222
01:31:50,498 --> 01:31:57,927
telling the person I love...
is the most wonderful thing in this world.

1223
01:32:06,514 --> 01:32:08,004
Wow, what strong wind!

1224
01:32:24,265 --> 01:32:25,732
Oh shut up.

1225
01:32:25,767 --> 01:32:28,463
Who cares about that,
it's the same either way!

1226
01:32:28,970 --> 01:32:30,562
No, we'll get scolded!

1227
01:32:30,805 --> 01:32:32,602
Yeah yeah, I'm out!

1228
01:32:33,108 --> 01:32:34,905
Hey wait!

